Java Loops Definition: 

Loops are used to execute a block of code repeatedly until a condition is satisfied. They hel. To reduce code repition and rerunning.


While Loop

Definition
A while loop executes a block of code as long as the given condition is true.
Working
First, the condition is checked.
If it is true, the loop body runs.
This continues until the condition becomes false.
Key Points
Condition is checked before execution
May not run even once if condition is false
Useful when the number of iterations is not known


Do-While Loop

Definition
A do-while loop executes the code block first and then checks the condition.
Working
The loop body runs once without checking the condition.
After execution, the condition is checked.
If true, it repeats; otherwise, it stops.
Key Points
Condition is checked after execution
Runs at least once, even if the condition is false
Commonly used in menu-driven programs


For Loop

Definition
A for loop is used when the number of iterations is known beforehand.
Working
It has three parts: initialization, condition, and update.
The loop runs as long as the condition is true, updating each time.
Key Points
More compact and readable
Best for counting loops
Commonly used in arrays and patterns
